## Automatically unlock GPG key on login
[Source](https://github.com/cruegge/pam-gnupg)

1. At the end of your /etc/system-local-login file, add:
```sh
auth	   optional	pam_gnupg.so
session    optional	pam_gnupg.so
```

2. In your `~/.gnupg/gpg-agent.conf` file, add:
```sh
allow-preset-passphrase
default-cache-ttl 86400
max-cache-ttl 86400
```

3. Run `gpg -K --with-keygrip`, and put the keygrip into `~/.config/pam-gnupg` file

4. Make sure that your GPG key and login passwords are identical.


## Setup pass
1. Import email password: `pass insert email`
2. Import nextcloud app password: `pass insert nextcloud`


## Setup crontab
Sync mail every 10 minutes
```sh
*/10 * * * * /home/chris/.local/bin/emailsync
```
